params.direct: True if `newOwner` should be set immediately. False if `newOwner` needs to use `claimOwnership`.
params.renounce: Allows the `newOwner` to be `address(0)` if `direct` and `renounce` is True. Has no effect otherwise.

auditReserves().notice: takes inventory of all tracked assetsalways consolidate to recognized reserves before audit

claimOwnership().notice: Needs to be called by `pendingOwner` to claim ownership.

incurDebt(uint256,address).notice: allow approved address to borrow reserves

mintRewards(address,uint256).notice: send epoch reward to staking contract

queue(uint8,address).notice: queue address to change boolean in mapping

repayDebtWithReserve(uint256,address).notice: allow approved address to repay borrowed reserves with reserves

repayDebtWithTime(uint256).notice: allow approved address to repay borrowed reserves with Time

toggle(uint8,address,address).notice: verify queue then set boolean in mapping

transferOwnership(address,bool,bool).notice: Transfers ownership to `newOwner`. Either directly or claimable by the new pending owner. Can only be invoked by the current `owner`.
